A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
To express the condolences of the Legislature of Louisiana upon the death of Charles James
"Charlie" Kirk, co-founder of Turning Point USA.
WHEREAS, Charlie Kirk was born on October 14, 1993, in Arlington Heights,
Illinois, where he attended Wheeling High School; he later studied at Harper College, a
public community college in the northwest Chicago suburb of Palatine, before leaving to
pursue a career in political activism; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Kirk co-founded Turning Point USA in 2012 with the help of his
early mentor, the late Bill Montgomery; he launched the conservative advocacy group as a
shoestring campus effort and built it into a well-funded national organization; he used the
success of Turning Point USA to found several affiliated groups, including Turning Point
Action and Turning Point Faith; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Kirk's success as a conservative political activist increased his
professional profile, and he became a widely-known media figure; he hosted "The Charlie
Kirk Show" on talk radio, regularly appeared on conservative media outlets, and addressed
both the 2024 Republican National Convention and the 2022 Conservative Political Action
Conference; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Kirk focused on campus activism, youth engagement, and faith-
based organizing; he was also the author of several books; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Kirk married Erika Frantzve in 2021, and he is survived by his wife
and their two children; he will be deeply missed, but the legacy of his work will live on
through those who were privileged to have known him.
